@eolivelli @tisonkun Would you mind take another look ? I reworked the fix:

1. Fix implementation of `interruptLeadership` to interrupt only if `hasLeadership`.
2. Use `ourThread` to cancel election, this avoids immature future task cancellation which break election loops. With help from synchronized `taskStarted`, `taskDone`, we can certainly know next election after `cancelElection` will see cancellation cause(e.g. session expired).

@kezhuw Thanks for your contribution!

Could you write a few flowchart to explain the effective execution before and after this patch?

I'm not very sure that we modify the node correct by reviewing the code and it takes a lot of time to reverse engineering :D
